Guardiola asked if LFC are worst possible opponents at 3-0 down.<br />
<br />
&quot;Yes, one of the worst. But Barcelona, Madrid, Bayern would say the same! When you see the quarter final draw, all of them are tough.&quot;

Guardiola asked about Otamendi form.<br />
<br />
&quot;Maybe (I will change). I have an idea of what we will do. But in Nico's case, when a player does what he has done, all we can is be close to him. Nico has huge quality and huge mentality.&quot;

Guardiola: &quot;We are in quarter finals of CL, and top of the league, and Otamendi is one of the reasons for that.&quot;<br />
<br />
Says John Stones was left out v United because he had an injury in training with England and they didn't want to risk him. &quot;He knows the confidence I have in him.&quot;

Klopp: &ldquo;That is not in the best place. He is receiving treatment and we&rsquo;re still hoping it will be a little bit quicker than maybe we thought in the first moment.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;But we cannot say anything else.&quot;
